OL,3,C'Unforgivable': Report finds death of
OL,4,Clearning disabled man was preventable
OL,6,FMyles' uncle Paul Scriven, who is a
OL,7,FLiberal Democrat peer in the House of
OL,8,FLords, told ITV News his nephew's
OL,9,Fdeath is "unforgivable", and accused
OL,10,Fthe Calderdale and Huddersfield NHS
OL,11,FTrust of being "more concerned with
OL,12,Fdefending its reputation than
OL,13,Fpreventing the deaths of people with
OL,14,Flearning disabilities".
OL,16,FLord Scriven said Myles' death must be
OL,17,Fa watershed moment in how people with
OL,18,Flearning disabilities are treated in
OL,19,Fthe health service.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/17
