OL,3,C'Unforgivable': Report finds death of
OL,4,Clearning disabled man was preventable
OL,6,F"There's lots of different things that
OL,7,Fcan be done, but unfortunately these
OL,8,Fopportunities were never afforded to
OL,9,FMyles, merely because he wasn't
OL,10,Fbelieved and because he was learning
OL,11,Fdisabled and autistic, he wasn't
OL,12,Freally able to engage in decisions
OL,13,Fabout his treatment."
OL,15,FOn July 11, 2025, the coroner in
OL,16,FBradford found that both a lack of
OL,17,Fadjustment for Myles' learning
OL,18,Fdisability and autism and neglect
OL,19,Fcontributed to his death.
