OL,3,C'Unforgivable': Report finds death of
OL,4,Clearning disabled man was preventable
OL,6,FHe found healthcare professionals had
OL,7,Fa 'complacent and dismissive attitude
OL,8,Ftowards Myles and his learning
OL,9,Fdisability', clinicians were 'blind'
OL,10,Fto his needs, and did not make
OL,11,Fsufficient reasonable adjustments for
OL,12,Fhis disability.
OL,14,FSpeaking in his first television
OL,15,Finterview to ITV News about Myles'
OL,16,Fdeath, Lord Scriven said "there is no
OL,17,Fdoubt" that Myles would still be alive
OL,18,Fif he did not have a learning
OL,19,Fdisability.
