OL,3,C'Unforgivable': Report finds death of
OL,4,Clearning disabled man was preventable
OL,6,FDuring the inquest, the NHS Trust
OL,7,Ftried to argue Myles did have mental
OL,8,Fcapacity to make his own decisions
OL,9,Fregarding his medical treatment.
OL,11,F"David knew Myles for 28 years of his
OL,12,Flife. I carried Myles in the first few
OL,13,Fhours of his life, and I carried him
OL,14,Fon my shoulder in his coffin to his
OL,15,Fgrave," said Lord Scriven.
OL,17,F"He didn't have capacity. They were
OL,18,Ftrying to tell us that people who had
OL,19,Fbeen with him for ten minutes knew him
OL,20,Fbetter than us."
